ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR DRONE OPERATION:

1. COMPLIANCE WITH AVIATION REGULATIONS
   Users must comply with all applicable local, national, and international 
   aviation regulations, including but not limited to:
   - FAA regulations (USA)
   - EASA regulations (Europe)
   - Transport Canada regulations (Canada)
   - CASA regulations (Australia)
   - Other applicable civil aviation authorities

2. SAFETY RESPONSIBILITIES
   - Users are solely responsible for safe operation of drone systems
   - This software is intended for educational and research purposes
   - Professional/commercial use requires appropriate certifications
   - Users must maintain visual line of sight with aircraft when required
   - Users must not operate in restricted airspace without proper authorization

3. LIABILITY DISCLAIMER
   - The authors disclaim all liability for accidents, injuries, or property damage
   - Users assume all risks associated with drone operation
   - This software should not be used in life-critical applications without
     appropriate safety redundancies and testing

4. EXPORT CONTROL
   - This software may be subject to export control laws
   - Users are responsible for compliance with applicable export regulations
   - Military or dual-use applications may require special licenses

5. THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
   This software incorporates components licensed under various terms:
